text: I just played Flash Hulk for the first time last night. What a disgusting brutal deck. I was playing against other competitive decks for christ's sake.

my coolest win: turn 1 entomb, turn 2 reanimate, turn 3 abrupt decay the animate dead, and I assembled: Carrion Feeder, Viscera Seer, Academy Rector, Dryad Arbor. Sac Academy Rector to get Dance of the Dead, animate Hulk again, sac to get Renegade Rallier and Grand Abolisher, Rallier gets back the Animate Dead getting Hulk again, etc.
I played through both a counterspell (abrupt decay) and a beast within (by assembling two sac outlets and eventually getting to grand abolisher)

thinking about if Protean Hulk wasn't banned, I would have gotten Boonweaver Giant on turn 2, but then the person who had the beast within would have just hit my Pattern of Rebirth and I wouldn't have gone off.

Protean Hulk is just........ so disgusting. It doesn't feel fair that you can assemble a creature-based combo, one person has a counterspell and another has beast within and you can still win through it and also leave the critical part of the combo out for a whole turn. (To be fair, the ADecay was a clutch play on my part, but still.)
I won't be surprised if it sees a ban. That wasn't even fair. Those were competitive decks for christ's sake lol.

I don't think Protean Hulk is THE strongest thing in the format still, but it's so close. It really pushes the boundaries of what should be permissible. Counterplay via holding mana open for all-purpose instants like Beast Within shouldn't get so easily ignored and played around on turn 3.
I think.

I played 5 games last night and won 4, but to be fair two of the games I played only one deck could really be described as competitive. But 3 of the games where every deck was competitive, I won 2. Moreover, two of the wins I had last night would have been impossible with Boonweaver instead of Hulk: one was a turn 2 flash win, and the other I would have had Pattern of Rebirth destroyed to stop the combo.

I thought Flash Hulk was just a strictly better upgrade over Boonweaver with the occasional win via Flash, but the subtlety in how it makes certain lines harder for opponents to respond to (e.g. how i dodged beast within) makes it just so much better, pushing into the realm of being broken.
(also I like that my deck doesn't need reveilark anymore to combo off, as reveilark was often a dead card)
so yeah, that's how i feel about hulk y'all.
